  PURPOSE
  This is the English source file for all PortPane UI strings. Every language
  translation file is a copy of this file with the <value> content translated.
  If you want to add or update a translation, start here — copy this file.

  HOW TO CONTRIBUTE A TRANSLATION
  1. Copy this file. Name the copy using the IETF language tag:
       French   → Strings.fr.resx
       Spanish  → Strings.es.resx
       Japanese → Strings.ja.resx
       Any other language → Strings.{ietf-tag}.resx
  2. In your copy, fill in the Language, Language Code, Translator, and Date
     fields in the header comment (top of the file).
  3. Translate ONLY the text between <value> and </value> tags.
  4. NEVER change <data name="..."> key names — the app uses them to find strings.
  5. Preserve any {0}, {1} placeholders exactly — they are replaced at runtime.
  6. Read TRANSLATING.md for the full guide and terminology reference.
  7. Agree to the CLA (see CLA.md) — required before your PR can be merged.
  8. Before starting, check open pull requests to avoid duplicate effort.

  XML FORMATTING WARNING
  This file must be valid XML. Common mistakes that break the file:
    - Using & instead of &amp;   (e.g. "Search &amp; Replace", not "Search & Replace")
    - Using < instead of &lt;    (e.g. "&lt;value&gt;" if needed literally)
    - Using > instead of &gt;    (rarely needed but: &gt;)
    - Forgetting to close tags   (<value>text</value> not <value>text)
  Validate your file at: https://www.xmlvalidation.com

  TRANSLATION EXAMPLE
  Before (English source):
    <data name="RefreshButton" xml:space="preserve"><value>Refresh</value></data>

  After (French translation):
    <data name="RefreshButton" xml:space="preserve"><value>Actualiser</value></data>

  Note: The data name="RefreshButton" part did NOT change. Only the value did.

  For more help, see: TRANSLATING.md
  CLA reminder: All contributions require CLA agreement. See: CLA.md
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-->
